org.corfudb.generator.distributions

Interface DataSet

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    Keys, OperationCount, Operations, Streams

    public interface DataSet
    This class defines a generic data distribution. A DataSet is used by operations that require data to execute (i.e. writing). Created by maithem on 7/14/17.

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods Default Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      List getDataSet()
      Return the whole data set.
      void populate()
      Populate the data set.
      default List sample(int num)
      Returns a random subset of the data.

    • Method Detail

      • populate

        void populate()
        Populate the data set.

      • sample

        default List sample(int num)
        Returns a random subset of the data. The default sampling method uses a uniform distribution, but other distributions can be used by the concrete classes.
        Parameters:
        num - number of data points
        Returns:
        random data points

        Return the whole data set.
